# Roadmap

## Phase 1 — Foundation

### Focus
Establish the strategic, product, and brand foundations of the company.

### Priorities
- define core company positioning
- refine product platform direction
- shape brand identity and public narrative
- establish market-facing documentation
- clarify regulatory direction at a high level
- organize early commercialization thinking
- build the initial public company repository and platform story

### Objective
Create a clear and coherent foundation for the company so that product, brand, market, and platform direction are aligned from the beginning.

### What Success Looks Like
- a clear brand and company identity
- a defined product platform narrative
- a strong public-facing story
- early strategic alignment across product, market, and technology
- a credible platform vision that can be presented externally

---

## Phase 2 — Product and Market Readiness

### Focus
Translate the company foundation into market-ready product and commercialization development.

### Priorities
- continue refining product concepts and formulation directions
- strengthen product messaging and category positioning
- prepare public-safe product materials
- develop go-to-market logic across relevant channels
- identify early partnership and distribution opportunities
- strengthen trust architecture through clearer documentation and presentation
- build a more structured commercialization narrative

### Objective
Move from concept and platform framing toward practical readiness for real-world market entry.

### What Success Looks Like
- clearer product-market fit signals
- stronger commercialization materials
- improved readiness for partnerships and outreach
- more confidence in the company’s category positioning
- a more operational go-to-market structure

---

## Phase 3 — Early Platform Expansion

### Focus
Expand from a company narrative into a more complete platform identity.

### Priorities
- broaden product-platform coherence across multiple use contexts
- deepen the connection between healing, recovery, and infection-control narratives
- strengthen educational and workflow-oriented materials
- create more structured operating documentation
- expand visual assets, diagrams, and presentation materials
- clarify how products, processes, and technology fit into one ecosystem

### Objective
Ensure that 9930 is understood not merely as a product effort, but as the foundation for a larger healing platform.

### What Success Looks Like
- a stronger platform-level identity
- clearer cross-category coherence
- improved ability to present the company as an expandable system
- stronger external understanding of long-term vision

---

## Phase 4 — Technology Integration

### Focus
Build the early intelligence and systems layer around the platform.

### Priorities
- develop the conceptual framework for AI-assisted symptom identification
- define SOP-based guidance pathways
- create the foundation for structured case intake and data collection
- build internal logic for process standardization
- explore how product workflows and digital workflows can connect
- strengthen the role of AI in both innovation and care-support infrastructure

### Objective
Begin transforming 9930 from a product-and-brand platform into a more intelligent and process-enabled system.

### What Success Looks Like
- a clear AI and workflow architecture
- structured logic for symptom identification and guidance
- better-defined data pathways
- stronger connection between care, process, and platform infrastructure

---

## Phase 5 — Data and Care Optimization

### Focus
Use structured feedback and data systems to improve care consistency and platform intelligence.

### Priorities
- collect and organize care-pathway data
- improve visibility into symptom and response patterns
- refine SOP logic over time
- support more consistent workflow execution
- build learning loops between cases, products, and process design
- strengthen the operational intelligence of the platform

### Objective
Create a system that not only delivers products and guidance, but also improves over time through structured learning.

### What Success Looks Like
- more reliable care workflows
- stronger process consistency
- better insight into platform performance
- more intelligent refinement of product and SOP pathways

---

## Phase 6 — Scaled Healing Platform

### Focus
Evolve 9930 into a broader, more integrated platform for healing, recovery, and infection-related care.

### Priorities
- unify products, workflows, knowledge, and technology into one coherent system
- strengthen multi-channel commercialization capability
- deepen platform defensibility through trust, systems, and execution
- expand support infrastructure around care journeys
- continue developing intelligent platform features
- position 9930 as a long-term category-defining platform

### Objective
Build a company that is not only recognized for products, but for a broader model of healing and platform-based care.

### What Success Looks Like
- a recognizable platform identity
- stronger expansion across categories and environments
- scalable integration of product and system layers
- a more complete, modern, and health-conscious healing ecosystem

---

## Roadmap Principles

The 9930 roadmap is guided by several core principles:

### Build in layers
The company is being developed step by step, with each layer strengthening the next.

### Preserve coherence
New products, systems, and narratives should reinforce one another rather than fragment the platform.

### Stay health-conscious
Growth should not come at the expense of the company’s underlying philosophy around healing, trust, and thoughtful product design.

### Modernize with purpose
Technology should not be added for appearance. It should improve clarity, consistency, scalability, and outcomes.

### Think beyond products
The long-term goal is not just to launch items, but to build a more complete healing platform.

---

## Current Position

9930 is currently in phase 1 for Canada and the US while it is in phase 3 for China.
This stage is essential because it defines how the company will scale in a disciplined and coherent way.

---

## Closing

The roadmap for 9930 is not based on the idea of growing a single product into a larger catalog.

It is based on a broader ambition:
to build a modern healing platform that combines health-conscious product development, TCM-inspired philosophy, structured commercialization, and intelligent technology support.

That is the direction of the company, and this roadmap is the framework for getting there.
